Porto, Villarreal and Benfica all
won easily at home to open their Europa League soccer
quarterfinals, while Braga tied 1-1 with  Dynamo Kiev .  Falcao scored a hat trick to lead Porto to a 5-1 win over
 Spartak Moscow . Nilmar scored twice as Villarreal routed FC
Twente 5-1 and two goals from Eduardo Salvio helped Benfica past
PSV Eindhoven 4-1.  Oleg Gusevâ€™s own goal gave Braga the draw at Dynamo Kiev,
which got a goal from Andriy Yarmolenko. Andriy Shevchenko was
sent off for Dynamo after receiving two yellow cards.  FC Twente, Spartak Moscow, PSV and Braga host the return
